[Rap]
Yo, listen up, it's the tale of the zebra, stripes of black and white
On the savannah, they stand divided, in a never-ending fight
Can't be tamed, can't be broken, spirits free and wild
Living in herds, yet they're plotting, a rivalry so vile

They battle for the grass, for the water, in a show of might
Screams and kicks, a brutal sight, but against the lion, it's a different plight
Blood runs the same, no matter the stripe, in the end, they're just the same type

This fabricated divide, this senseless hate, it's time to take a different route
Under the sun, they're painted in shades, but deep down, it's a facade
Zebra, zebra, hear the call, let go of the past, stand tall

[Outro]
In the end, it doesn't even matter, the stripes fade away
What remains is the heart, the courage, the will to stay
Zebra, zebra, in the end, it's not black or white
It's the unity, the survival, the eternal fight.

